  },
  {
    title: "What We Scale Startups helps with.",
    body: "We help founders and growth teams build this loop across the areas that matter most — clarifying ICP, sharpening positioning, identifying the anti-customer, improving the website journey, designing better experiments, and building AI-discoverable assets that turn insight into pipeline.",
    points: [
      "Growth audits, positioning work, and website strategy.",
      "AI-generated tools, founder-led content systems, GEO and SEO assets.",
      "Outbound experiments, sales enablement, drip email, and referral loops.",
      "The goal is not more marketing tasks — it is a growth system that compounds."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "Find your Learning Latency Score.",
    body: "Your biggest growth bottleneck may not be traffic, content, ads, or sales. It may be the delay between what the market is telling you and what your company does next. The diagnostic scores six areas from 1 to 5 and names the highest-leverage fix.",
    points: [
      "Signal Capture and Insight Quality — are you collecting and reading the market clearly?",
      "Experiment Design and Asset Velocity — do activities teach you something, and does insight become assets quickly?",
      "Feedback Memory — does every experiment improve the next decision?",
      "AI Discoverability — can buyers and AI systems understand and recommend you?"
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "AI will not fix weak positioning. It will expose it faster.",
    body: "In AI-native markets, products change fast and buyers are still forming their beliefs — which makes positioning more important, not less. The companies that win will not be the ones producing the most. They will be the ones learning fastest.",
    points: [
      "Growth = Signal Quality × Learning Speed × Execution Velocity × Feedback Memory.",
      "Signal beats volume; learning speed beats campaign speed.",
      "Your website is now a training layer for buyers, search engines, and AI assistants.",
      "Memory is the moat — everyone has similar tools; few have a richer memory of the market."
    ]
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is AI Driven Growth?",
    answer:
      "A methodology for building a Growth Signal Loop — a system that captures market signals, turns them into sharper positioning and experiments, and feeds every result back so the company learns faster. The aim is to reduce the time between market signal and revenue."
  },
  {
    question: "How is this different from using AI to automate marketing?",
    answer:
      "Automation produces more output. AI Driven Growth uses AI to learn faster. AI makes execution cheap, so volume is no longer the advantage — signal quality, learning speed, and market memory are. We use AI to sharpen judgement, not just to ship more."
  },
  {
